Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.75,0:00:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's the last\Nof it, Filthy Rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.27,0:00:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Just Rich, please. And on behalf\Nof Rich's Barnyard Bargains,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.51,0:00:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,thanks for another season's\Nshipment of Zap Apple Jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.43,0:00:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Our pleasure. See\Nya next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.82,0:00:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, Apple Bloom? Did you pack up\Nthe cider into the same crates
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.47,0:00:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as the Zap Apple Jam?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.16,0:00:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure did! Now that\NI'm getting older,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.51,0:00:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to prove I can handle\Nmore responsibility on the farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.05,0:00:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But the crates aren't marked.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.96,0:00:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You kept track of what when\Ninto which crate, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.06,0:00:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Um... Yep. I totally\Nkept track of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.76,0:00:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Because we wouldn't want\NFilthy Rich to get a shipment
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.77,0:00:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of cider when he's supposed\Nto get Zap Apple Jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.79,0:00:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You know how Granny\Nfeels about selling cider
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.26,0:00:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere but\Non the farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.02,0:00:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure he\Ngot the right crates?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.19,0:00:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, I'm sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.36,0:01:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now why don't you and Big\NMac head on out to the house
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.87,0:01:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and let me finish up here!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.66,0:01:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If you gave Rich the Zap Apple\NJam, then what's this here?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.14,0:01:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... Extra?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.81,0:01:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Nnope!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.92,0:01:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Regular subtitles\NBy YayPonies\N#APPLEJACK2016 - MAKE CIDER ALCOHOLIC AGAIN!\Nhttps://yp1.yayponies.eu
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.15,0:02:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny knows I wasn't trying\Nto make off with a shipment
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.76,0:02:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,of cider, right? Because\NI would never do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.58,0:02:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. We know\Nexactly whose fault it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.63,0:02:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, why in tarnation would\Nyou lie to me, Apple Bloom?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.92,0:02:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I was kinda hoping I could fix\Nit before anypony found out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.55,0:02:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Telling lies won't fix\Nanything. Trust me, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.49,0:02:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What could you\Npossibly know about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.37,0:02:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You've never told a\Nlie in your whole life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.77,0:02:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What's so funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.72,0:02:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, sugar cube, your\Nbig sister lied so much
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.16,0:02:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,when she was a filly, the whole\Nfamily ended up in the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.42,0:02:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,WHAT?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.42,0:02:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Eeyup.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.62,0:02:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You might as well\Ntell her the whole story.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.06,0:02:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It might even do\Nher some good.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.13,0:02:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,When Applejack and Big Mac\Nwere just a wee bit older
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.69,0:03:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,than you are now, they\Nboth kept squabblin' over
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.34,0:03:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,who would run\Nthe farm better.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.02,0:03:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All I'm sayin' is that you\Nmay have plenty of brawn,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.71,0:03:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm the one with the\Nideas on how to run things
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.16,0:03:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,better around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.36,0:03:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Applejack, Applejack,\NApplejack.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.98,0:03:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Ideas are all\Nwell and good,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.81,0:03:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but you can't plow\Na field with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.11,0:03:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how many\Ntimes I've told you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.02,0:03:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Too many!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.05,0:03:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You two horned toads better stop\Njabberin' and get to workin'!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.07,0:03:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah they'd better! I\Nneed you to go to town.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.94,0:03:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The apple blight's been awful\Nand if we don't get more spray,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.38,0:03:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,cider season'll be shorter\Nthan a dwarf crab-apple tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.52,0:03:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I was just telling\Ncousin Braeburn last week;
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.76,0:03:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,now there's a pony who knows how\Nto put his back into a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.95,0:03:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh hi there, Filthy Rich!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.26,0:03:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Just Rich, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.75,0:03:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd like you to meet\Nmy fianc√©e, Spoiled Milk.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.69,0:03:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Honey, this is\NApplejack and Big Mac,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.32,0:03:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the two hardest-working\Nponies at Sweet Apple Acres.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.48,0:04:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You work on a farm?\NHow... quaint.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.94,0:04:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh ho now,\Ndear, be nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.28,0:04:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Sweet Apple Acres\Nmakes Zap Apple Jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.64,0:04:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's one of Dad's\Nbest-sellers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.58,0:04:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean one of\Nyour best-sellers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.31,0:04:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,My amazing husband-to-be\Nis running the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.48,0:04:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Rich family business now. Did\Nyou know that? Well, now you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.71,0:04:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mind Spoiled Milk.\NShe's just proud of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.07,0:04:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But she's right; I'm in\Ncharge of the store now
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.09,0:04:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm just bursting\Nwith ideas I wanna try.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.33,0:04:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Like what?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.60,0:04:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how about this? Cider\Nseason's around the corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.77,0:04:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not let me\Nsell it for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.55,0:04:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That is an\Ninteresting idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.73,0:04:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe it's interesting\Nand maybe it ain't,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.67,0:04:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's definitely\Nnot a new idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.86,0:04:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny Smith told us your\Ngrandpa, Stinkin' Rich,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.40,0:04:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,used to ask her every year\Nif he could sell our cider
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.72,0:04:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in your store, and Granny\Ntold him every year
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.38,0:04:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,about the tradition of\Neverypony in Ponyville
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.66,0:04:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,lining up out at\NSweet Apple Acres.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.66,0:04:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, start a new tradition!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.95,0:05:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Someday one of you'll\Ntake over the farm
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.38,0:05:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,just like I've taken\Nover the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.06,0:05:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm guessing it'll be the\None with the best ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.12,0:05:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, as I've said\Nmany a time before,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.47,0:05:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,ideas are all well and good,\Nbut you can't plow a field--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.51,0:05:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what? How about\Nwe give you three barrels
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.39,0:05:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of cider early, and\Nif it sells well,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.81,0:05:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll make a deal\Nfor the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.41,0:05:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hey now! Perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.83,0:05:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, honey. I've got\Nto get everything ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.20,0:05:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoo-wee, I tell ya, if the\Nfuture means me running
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.35,0:05:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Sweet Apple Acres and you\Nbeing quiet, I can't wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.58,0:05:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I just can't believe you'd\Nmake a deal with Filthy Rich
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.75,0:05:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,without even talking to Granny.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.55,0:05:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Aw, Granny will love the\Nidea and then she'll decide
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.52,0:05:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm the one who should\Ntake over the farm. You'll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.80,0:05:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,See what?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.98,0:05:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Applejack here had another\None of her "big ideas,"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.67,0:05:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and I think we all know my\Nposition on ideas, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.33,0:06:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,...can't plow a\Nfield with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.01,0:06:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Eey... Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.17,0:06:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Big idea, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.95,0:06:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, more of\Nan opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.11,0:06:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, we ran into\NFilthy Rich in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.50,0:06:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you know he's running\Nthe family store now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.49,0:06:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And what does this\Nhere "opportunity"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.03,0:06:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,mean for Sweet\NApple Acres?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.47,0:06:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, since cider season is\Nalmost here, he or, I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.27,0:06:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it'd be a good idea to\Ngive him a few barrels of cider
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.99,0:06:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to sell at the store\Nbefore the season starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.44,0:06:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that all?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.88,0:06:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely not!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.74,0:06:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.93,0:06:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But Granny, why can't we sell\Na few barrels of cider early
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.99,0:06:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to Filthy Rich? How's it any\Ndifferent than when you gave
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.20,0:06:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Zap Apple Jam to Filthy's\Ngrandpappy to sell?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.97,0:06:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Your cider and your jam\Nain't the same thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.66,0:06:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Zap Apple Jam jars preserve\Nthe flavor for moons,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.60,0:06:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but cider starts to spoil
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.58,0:07:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the second it comes\Nout of the press.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.71,0:07:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why every cider season,\Nall of Ponyville lines up
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.42,0:07:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,at Sweet Apple Acres and first\Ncome is first served. Hmm!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.23,0:07:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I get what you're\Nsaying, Granny,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.32,0:07:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,but couldn't you make an\Nexception just this once?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.67,0:07:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I sorta promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.28,0:07:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Meh-eh. Besides, cider-makin'\Nis iffy business.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.26,0:07:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're probably not gonna\Nhave a lot this year anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.79,0:07:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,what with all the blight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.15,0:07:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Applejack, but\Nyou'll have to un-promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.98,0:07:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.39,0:07:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to say I told\Nyou so, Applejack, but--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.31,0:07:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You and I both know you\Ndon't hate to say anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.84,0:07:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I've always thought\Nthat the most important thing
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.71,0:07:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,a pony can do is say\Nexactly what's on his mind
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.10,0:07:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to anypony who'll listen\Nso everypony everywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.63,0:07:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,always knows everything\Nyou're thinking and...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.97,0:07:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't ever have to\Nlisten to anypony else.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.08,0:07:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.74,0:07:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.56,0:08:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if it ain't my\Nnew business partner!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.03,0:08:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, about the\Ncider, Rich...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.70,0:08:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a look at what I did last\Nnight after we made our deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.92,0:08:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Woo! Pretty great, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.33,0:08:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing is, I don't\Nthink I can get you any.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.36,0:08:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What?! But I did all\Nthis work on your say-so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.48,0:08:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We shook hooves and\Neverything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.35,0:08:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see, at\NSweet Apple Acres,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.36,0:08:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,we've always been about quality\Nand while your basic jam jar'll-
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.75,0:08:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus it's been a tough\Nharvest this year,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.91,0:08:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,what with all the\Nblight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.07,0:08:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds to me like you're\Ntrying to make excuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.33,0:08:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever Granddad dealt with\NGranny Smith, she kept her word.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.73,0:08:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can't do that,\Nthen maybe our families
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.46,0:08:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,should stop doing business\Ntogether. Altogether!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.37,0:08:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now, the thing is, Rich,\Nit ain't really up to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.65,0:08:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, Granny's--
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.09,0:08:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,--sick!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.97,0:08:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait. Granny's\Nsick? I had no idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.66,0:09:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Eey... Yeah, nopony did.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.28,0:09:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What Big Mac means is we've\Nbeen trying to keep it quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.91,0:09:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't want people\Nto make rash decisions
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.69,0:09:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,about doing business\Nwith Sweet Apple Acres
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.62,0:09:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,just because we're a little\Nshort-hooved at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.65,0:09:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my! Of course, of\Ncourse. I am so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.50,0:09:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Please let me know if\Nthere's anything I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.11,0:09:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Much appreciated. But\Nright now, we only ask
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.69,0:09:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,for your understanding\Nduring this difficult time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.09,0:09:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.39,0:09:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Big Mac: You were supposed to\Ntell Rich the simple truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.62,0:09:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but instead you made things\Nworse with a giant lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.42,0:09:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what was I supposed\Nto do? You heard Rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.71,0:09:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If I told him the truth, he\Nwas gonna stop doing business
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.37,0:09:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,with us altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.72,0:09:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but that's\Nonly because--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.31,0:09:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,--I forgot to ask if we\Nhad any oat crumbles
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.77,0:09:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,for this delicious-looking\Nsalad, Granny!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.16,0:09:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.56,0:09:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,--that was only because you made\Npromises you couldn't keep,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.14,0:09:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but there's gotta be a\Nbetter way out of this mess
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.99,0:10:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,than by making up some story\Nabout Granny being sick!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.03,0:10:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it worked, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.15,0:10:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to drop by unannounced.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.87,0:10:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We just wanted to come by to\Nwish Granny a speedy recovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.82,0:10:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, sis, our good friend Mr.\NRich and his fianc√©e are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.87,0:10:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, and they brought\Nflowers. For Granny.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.53,0:10:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,On account of she's sick, like\Nyou said. Ain't that sweet?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.03,0:10:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, excuse me one second!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.07,0:10:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What in tarnation?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.16,0:10:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm sorry, Granny.\NI didn't see you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.91,0:10:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You came blasting in so fast,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.68,0:10:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,t'weren't possible\Nto see nothin'!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.44,0:10:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you go out to the barn?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.76,0:10:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I, uh, I think we might\Nhave left a blight sprayer
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.34,0:10:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,in the orchard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.32,0:10:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you outta your apple-pickin'\Nmind? It's suppertime, girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.86,0:10:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, but if we\Nforgot a sprayer,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.25,0:10:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd wanna get it before\Ndark. You go start counting
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.02,0:10:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'll tell Big Mac\Nwe'll be right back, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.67,0:11:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So from that moment on, I\Ntook to referring to myself
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.59,0:11:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,as Big or Large or--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.72,0:11:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh Applejack, your brother\Nwas just explaining
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.61,0:11:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,why he always wears his yoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.12,0:11:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though we asked him how\Nyour grandmare is doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.84,0:11:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you know how Big\NMac can get to talking,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.07,0:11:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,especially when he's\Nupset. And right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.45,0:11:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,he's just as worried about\NGranny Smith as I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.16,0:11:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh dear. Is she doing that bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.39,0:11:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, one thing's for sure,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.31,0:11:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,she shouldn't be seeing\Nanypony right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.54,0:11:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I'm getting more\Nupset just thinking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.77,0:11:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.24,0:11:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, what in the frilly\Nfumidila has gotten into you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.04,0:11:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Granny! I just\Ndecided if I helped you,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.25,0:11:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,it would go faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.73,0:11:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you're too late.\NAll the sprayers are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.42,0:12:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, good. Uh say, Granny,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.87,0:12:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,when did you first fight\Nthe apple blight again?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.82,0:12:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It was my second year\Nhere in Ponyville
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.15,0:12:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and that was before I had\Nthe rick on the one knee.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.83,0:12:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,...and others say that's how the\Ntrees got to growing so tall,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.80,0:12:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but to me, it's just\Nhow I got my cutie mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.97,0:12:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But we asked when we could\Ncome back to see Granny!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.45,0:12:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Big Mac didn't\Nwant to be rude,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.17,0:12:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but you just can't see Granny\Nright now because she's...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.57,0:12:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,...got apple blight!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.87,0:12:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought only trees\Ngot the blight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.61,0:12:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's\Nusually the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.21,0:12:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The doctors think it's from\Nworking in the orchard
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.50,0:12:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,for so many years.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.60,0:12:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You see. We had to take\NGranny to Ponyville General.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.11,0:12:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We just got back right\Nbefore you showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.79,0:12:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, that is terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.71,0:12:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Eww, it's not\Ncontagious, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.98,0:13:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, I'm sure you'll be\Nfine, but you should leave,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.44,0:13:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.09,0:13:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right. We're gonna have\Nto hurry if we want to get there
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.34,0:13:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,before visiting hours are over.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.87,0:13:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. Wait. Get where?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.91,0:13:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, the hospital, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.99,0:13:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure we'll see you there!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.93,0:13:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Telling Filthy Rich that\NGranny's in the hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.02,0:13:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,just made everything\Na hundred times worse!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.21,0:13:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we supposed to do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.17,0:13:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.93,0:13:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,...dropped my second best\Nteeth right in the pig pen
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.89,0:13:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and that was the worst case of\Napple blight I've ever seen!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.39,0:13:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd love to hear\Nmore Granny,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.99,0:13:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,but we gotta get to the\Nhospital right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.46,0:13:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The hospital?\NWhy, who's sick?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.52,0:13:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You are, apparently.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.82,0:13:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What he means is, you're\Nneeded at the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.70,0:13:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever for?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.57,0:13:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the apple blight! It's\Nstarting to infect ponies now!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.02,0:14:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The doctors need an expert\Nopinion, and nopony knows more
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.45,0:14:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,about fighting blight\Nthan Granny Smith!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.43,0:14:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what in tarnation are\Nwe waiting for? Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.09,0:14:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, we're supposed\Nto go in the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.62,0:14:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, to avoid anypony in the\Nwaiting room with the blight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.14,0:14:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oops, I almost forgot!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.34,0:14:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.24,0:14:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you don't have to worry\Nabout catching the blight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.03,0:14:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If you say so, dearie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.91,0:14:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you wait right here while\NI... check on your presentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.75,0:14:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What in the rotten\Nrhubarb's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.06,0:14:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Fancy meeting you two here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.34,0:14:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we told you\Nwe were coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.96,0:14:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm glad we found you\Nbecause I can't seem to find
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.82,0:15:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny's room, or any\Nnurses who've even heard
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.94,0:15:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,about a pony with\Napple blight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.21,0:15:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny's room. Sure. Just\Ngo down here, take a left,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.82,0:15:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,then a right, go down some\Nstairs, up a bunch more stairs,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.70,0:15:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,through the cafeteria,\Nleft three more times
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.71,0:15:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you're there. Easy as\NGranny's apple pie! Heh heh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.89,0:15:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you coming with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.55,0:15:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll catch up! I\Ngotta find Big Mac.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.10,0:15:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, Granny, just wait here\None second and we can go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.81,0:15:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you\Ntwo going?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.35,0:15:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Big Mac can't come.\NHe, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.58,0:15:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,...might be contagious.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.95,0:15:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Contagious?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.65,0:15:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Climb up here\Nand I'll cover you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.54,0:15:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll bring Rich in,\Ntell him you're Granny,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.87,0:15:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're not allowed\Nto take the sheets off.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.47,0:15:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You moan a few times, he leaves,\Nand this whole thing is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.11,0:15:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This is spinnin' way out\Nof control, Applejack!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.20,0:15:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I know you thought selling\Ncider in Filthy's store
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.51,0:15:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,was a good idea, but it\Nain't worth lying to him
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.44,0:15:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,about Granny being sick and\Nneedin' to go to the hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.51,0:15:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,or fibbin' to Granny about\Nthem wanting her to come here
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.22,0:16:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to talk about the blight, or--
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.74,0:16:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,BIG MACINTOSH, PLEASE JUST\NLISTEN TO ME FOR ONCE!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.62,0:16:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This ain't about my ideas!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.54,0:16:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If Rich finds out\Nabout all the lies,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.64,0:16:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,he'll cut ties with us and\Nthe farm will go under.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.28,0:16:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now do you want that to\Nhappen or do you wanna help?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.49,0:16:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can't you be Granny?\NYou're her size,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.36,0:16:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is all your fault\Nin the first place!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.99,0:16:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I would, but if I let\Nyou do the talkin',
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.77,0:16:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd just ramble on and on\Nuntil we all got caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.00,0:16:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Just lay down, keep still
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.79,0:16:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and promise me you won't say\Nanything for once in your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.45,0:16:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Eeyup.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.02,0:16:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.75,0:16:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.56,0:16:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about time. What\Nis going on around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.05,0:16:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny, they need you to wait\Nhere. I'll come get you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.09,0:16:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There you are! We've\Nbeen going in circles
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.19,0:16:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,looking for Granny's room!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.12,0:16:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you're in luck, 'cause\Nit's, it's right over here
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.49,0:17:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and this time I'll make\Nsure you don't get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.41,0:17:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What in the dadgum?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.09,0:17:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.12,0:17:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He-- I mean, "she"\Nwas right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.97,0:17:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no! We gotta go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.86,0:17:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that\NGranny Smith?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.18,0:17:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are they\Ntaking her?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.59,0:17:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You two, don't lose\Nthat gurney!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.70,0:17:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny, what're you doin'? You\Nwere supposed to stay there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.86,0:17:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a supply closet!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.55,0:17:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Uh, well, OK, come\Nwith me, but be quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.45,0:17:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, save your voice\Nfor the big presentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.56,0:18:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but you can't get any\Ncloser without a gown and mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.49,0:18:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But-- but-but that's\Nmy brother on there!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.18,0:18:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. This\Nis our best doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.89,0:18:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,She'll have your brother back\Non his hooves in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.68,0:18:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, apple blight is\Na serious disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.96,0:18:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then? Did she say\N"apple blight?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.72,0:18:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I think she said\N"gasket mites."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.26,0:18:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And once the trunk\Nturns red like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.85,0:18:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the only thing to do\Nis prune the branches.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.29,0:18:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no! Granny!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.87,0:18:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you say "prune\Nthe branches?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.06,0:18:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, sure. What\Nelse you gonna do
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.68,0:18:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,once the blight\Ngets this bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.39,0:18:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Everypony just stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.36,0:19:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all a big\Nmisunderstanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.49,0:19:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, it's a big lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.55,0:19:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Big Mac?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.30,0:19:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny Smith? What is\Ngoing on here, Applejack?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.77,0:19:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a darn\Ngood question.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.56,0:19:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure if I was worried\Nthat nopony was listening
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.43,0:19:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to my ideas or just nervous\Nthat I wouldn't be the one
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.44,0:19:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to end up running the farm,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.01,0:19:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but I promised\Nsomething to Filthy Rich
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.28,0:19:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that I couldn't deliver and I\Nwas too embarrassed to admit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.64,0:19:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So Granny was never sick?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.08,0:19:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And there ain't no\Napple blight in ponies?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.35,0:19:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.94,0:19:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Those were all lies. And I\Nthought if you found out,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.94,0:19:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd stop doing\Nbusiness with the farm,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.41,0:19:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so I just kept\Ntelling more.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.21,0:19:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, she's not a doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.44,0:19:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't make Granny and\Nthe farm suffer for what I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.82,0:19:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This whole thing is my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.06,0:19:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not\Nentirely true.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.31,0:20:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe if I paid more attention\Nto what you had to say
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.51,0:20:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of talking\Nall the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.21,0:20:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,none of this would have\Nhappened in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.53,0:20:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I just need to talk\Nless and listen more...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.38,0:20:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.69,0:20:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, big brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.10,0:20:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And whether it's me running\NSweet Apple Acres or you,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.38,0:20:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it'll be in good hooves.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.26,0:20:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's nice, but I\Ndon't know what in blazes
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.25,0:20:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you two are talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.67,0:20:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I ain't going anywhere anytime\Nsoon. Pfft! Running the farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.67,0:20:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Not after this\Ndisplay. Not likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.53,0:20:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't you go getting any\Nideas about "cutting ties"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.70,0:20:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,with Sweet Apple Acres, or I'm\Ngoin right to your grandpappy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.23,0:20:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Get me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.29,0:20:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.52,0:20:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, who here still wants to\Nhear about the apple blight?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.98,0:20:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now when I was a filly...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.46,0:20:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe you\Ntold all those lies!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.52,0:20:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a story I'm\Nproud of,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.02,0:21:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,but it taught me a lifelong\Nlesson about being honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.76,0:21:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you learned\Nsomething too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.17,0:21:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I sure did! I learned that\Nno pony starts out perfect
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.90,0:21:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and sometimes you gotta\Nmake a few mistakes
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.28,0:21:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to figure out who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.12,0:21:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Eeyup!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.50,0:21:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But I think the most\Nimportant thing I learned
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.57,0:21:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is who really runs\NSweet Apple Acres...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.43,0:21:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.85,0:21:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yer darn tootin'! Now everypony\Nquit yer lolly-gaggery
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.95,0:21:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and get back to work. Right\Nafter we have a glass of cider!
